1) to know python libraries you installed
    
    pip list


2) installing virtualenv:
    pip install virtualenv
    
3) creating virtualenv:
    virtualenv -p python3.8 dj4
    
4) cd dj4/
5) activate the virtualenv:
    source bin/activate

6) installing django:
    pip install django

7) making the src folder in dj4 :
     mkdir src

8) cd src
9) starting the project :
    django-admin startproject blog .
10) runnig server :
    python manage.py runserver
11) to fix migrate error :
    python manage.py migrate
12) to run the page:
    http://127.0.0.1:8000/
13) to get in admin page :
    http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin
14) creating username $ password:
    python manage.py createsuperuser
15) to start new app :
    django-admin startapp post  ( post is the name of the app)
16) after making database for the app you need to migrate these updates :
    python manage.py makemigrations
    python manage.py migrate
